other_tests.findings: The liver is normal in morphology and signal intensity. No focal liver lesion is identified. The biliary tree is normal without intra or extrahepatic bile duct dilation. Multiple layering stones are seen within the gallbladder. Gallbladder wall edema is nonspecific in the setting of mild intra-abdominal ascites. The pancreas demonstrates normal signal intensity and enhancement with a small amount of peripancreatic stranding. The pancreatic duct is normal in caliber. There is an accessory spleen noted. The left kidney is malrotated and lies within the midline. No hydronephrosis or renal lesion is identified. The uterus is enlarged, compatible with postpartum state. No osseous abnormality is identified. There is diffuse body wall edema.
